# NewsArticle_RAG

AI-powered News Article Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) System using Python.

---

## Overview

This project implements a **RAG pipeline** for news articles.  
It leverages:

- **Vector database** for storing embeddings  
- **LLM integration** for generating summaries or answers  
- **Chunking** and **embedding storage** for efficient retrieval  

Designed for **research, experimentation, and AI demos**.

---

## Features

- Load and process news articles  
- Store embeddings in a vector database  
- RAG-based querying for articles  
- Modular architecture for easy experimentation  
- Secure handling of API keys via `.env`

---

## Quick Start

Clone the repository and install dependencies in one go:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/vijayyy-code/NewsArticle_RAG.git
cd NewsArticle_RAG
python -m venv venv && venv\Scripts\activate && pip install -r requirements.txt
Note for Linux/Mac:
Use source venv/bin/activate instead of venv\Scripts\activate.

Set up your .env file in the root:

env
Copy code
API_KEY=your_api_key_here
.env is ignored in GitHub for security.

Usage
Run the RAG pipeline:

bash
Copy code
python main.py
Other modules:

chunking.py → split articles into chunks

embedding_store.py → manage embeddings

llm_integration.py → interface with LLMs

rag_pipeline.py → run RAG queries

check.py / remove.py → utility scripts

Folder Structure
csharp
Copy code
newsrag/
├── cache/               # temporary cache files (ignored)
├── vector_db/           # vector database (ignored)
├── venv/                # virtual environment (ignored)
├── __pycache__/         # Python cache (ignored)
├── app.py
├── main.py
├── chunking.py
├── embedding_store.py
├── llm_integration.py
├── rag_pipeline.py
├── remove.py
├── check.py
├── requirements.txt
├── .env.example
├── .gitignore
